## Third-party data sources

This project consumes character stroke data from several upstream sources,
each with its own license. The MIT license above applies only to the
stroke-order Python code; data fetched / bundled at runtime retains its
original license:

- g0v/zh-stroke-data — see https://github.com/g0v/zh-stroke-data for
  licensing terms (derived from MOE 教育部 standard kaishu data).
- Make Me a Hanzi — LGPL 3.0 (https://github.com/skishore/makemeahanzi).
- KanjiVG — CC BY-SA 3.0 (https://github.com/KanjiVG/kanjivg).
- 教育部標準楷書 / 隸書 / 宋體 — Republic of China Ministry of Education;
  consult the MOE font terms before redistributing the TTF files.
- 全字庫 (CNS 11643) — Taiwan Government Open Data (政府資料開放授權條款 1.0).
- 崇羲篆體 — CC BY-ND, by 季旭昇 + Institute of Information Science,
  Academia Sinica.

When redistributing or deploying this project, ensure compliance with the
license of each data source you choose to bundle.
